<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> have eyes in the back of one’s head • have one’s head screwed on backwards</xh5><p> <i>have eyes in the back of one’s head—</i>said of the ability to know what happens even if one is not looking: I remember thinking my mom must <u>have eyes in the back of her head</u> when she would know what I was doing without even turning around to see.</p><p> <i>have one’s head screwed on backwards—</i>lack common sense; behave in a strange and irrational way: I <u>had my head screwed on backwards</u> when I was packing my things, so I left all my Baltimore telephone numbers in my desk in Towson! <i>Cf.: have one’s head screwed on the right way</i>—(also: have one’s head screwed on right) be wise and sensible; act in a reasonable way: The general remark was that Colin <u>had his head screwed on the right way</u> and that some day he would come out on top.</p> </entry>
